l cycles of our planet. These glacial periods or ice ages have ended as NHHLSI peaks have set off the oxidation of oceanic oozes and greenhouse warming. The current warming is not associated with a NHHLSI peak.\nIt good to understand how our world works, so that we can manage it properly.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "123713559", "causal_relations": [{"cause": null, "effect": "oxidation of southern ocean high carbon oozes and 10,000 of greenhouse warming"}, {"cause": "a peak in northern hemisphere", "effect": "the last glacial period ended 9,000 years ago high latitude solar insolation"}]}, {"id": "123722309", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544746627000}, "author": "paulswann", "author_id": "4710219", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "More accurately, a change of system is required. Perpetual growth-obsessed capitalism must end. De-growth and an ecological civilisation (as Jeremy Lent calls it) must begin, imminently. There Is No Alternative. Seriously, and shouting, THERE IS NO ALTERNATIVE.", "recommendation_count": "5", "in_reply_to": "123713082", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "123722204", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544746145000}, "author": "Michael Kirney", "author_id": "14729167", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Not sure what 'wet bulb' means, but daytime highs in my part of Ontario hit 35 C on a regular basis in July and August, 2015 and 2016.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "123718931", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "123722176", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544746020000}, "author": "Michael Kirney", "author_id": "14729167", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "So do they grow grapes in Kent now? Grapes are actually very hardy and adaptable, and there are dozens of different varieties. I bet there is one that would take Kent very well.", "recommendation_count": "3", "in_reply_to": "123720784", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "123722164", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544