ery short time rents on the south side of the river were found to have risen about sixpence a week, or the amount of the toll which had been remitted!\nAnd a friend of mine was telling me the other day that, in the parish of Southwark, about 350 pounds a year was given away in doles of bread by charitable people in connection with one of the churches. As a consequence of this charity, the competition for small houses and single-room tenements is so great that rents are considerably higher in the parish!\"\nThe full text of this once-famous speech is given here.http://www.landvaluetax.org/current-affairs-comment/winston-churchill-said-it-all-better-then-we-can.html\nSo, completely orthodox. If it seems unfamiliar, it is because an important stream of thinking in political economy has been lost in the past 100 years. It is one reason why policies rarely have the intended effect and often have the opposite effect.", "recommendation_count": "1", "in_reply_to": "123449453", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "an important stream of thinking in political economy has been lost in the past 100 years", "effect": "if it seems unfamiliar it is"}]}, {"id": "123451825", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544192890000}, "author": "clayfin", "author_id": "4410260", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "This comment was removed by a moderator because it didn't abide by our\ncommunity standards.\nReplies may also be deleted. For more detail see our FAQs.", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "it did n't abide by our community standards", "effect": "this comment was removed by a moderator"}]}, {"id": "123451791", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544192854000}, "author": "shedexile", "author_id": "12183741", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "The problem is obvious (to state the bleeding obvious)....\nIf public transport is not a more attractive option (in terms of cost, access, reliabilty, relative comfort etc), people will continue to use cars.\nIt is pointless trying 