en going on for a couple of million years.\nThere is no consensus of the kind you quoted.\nYou've been hoodwinked.", "recommendation_count": "12", "in_reply_to": "123706788", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "123701908", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544709032000}, "author": "Lillianne", "author_id": "14670089", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Like it or not, a forest is razed, a new city is built, and the air currents in the region change. They aren't walled in. They reach into the surround which reaches in to a wider surround until the change is global. Meanwhile, increase the CO2 content of the air and... well, it's pointless claiming much isn't human made.\nIt's a matter of looking at it as a system... everything is functionally related.", "recommendation_count": "0", "in_reply_to": "123700731", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "123709658", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544719065000}, "author": "barrie9", "author_id": "17315996", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "This comment was removed by a moderator because it didn't abide by our\ncommunity standards.\nReplies may also be deleted. For more detail see our FAQs.", "causal_relations": [{"cause": "it did n't abide by our community standards", "effect": "this comment was removed by a moderator"}]}, {"id": "123709635", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544719038000}, "author": "xwookey", "author_id": "4307215", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "Plenty of scientific institutions have good explanations of this. I suggest you read one rather than one of us typing it all out again:https://royalsociety.org/topics-policy/projects/climate-change-evidence-causes/NASA has good info too.", "recommendation_count": "10", "in_reply_to": "123706472", "causal_relations": null}, {"id": "123701742", "time_stamp": {"$date": 1544708827000}, "author": "Lillianne", "author_id": "14670089", "schema_org_type": "http://schema.org/Comment", "text": "I reckon it's already too late. The c